parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Soft Brake Pedal and Increased Stopping Distance
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The soft brake pedal and increased stopping distance can lead to accidents, injuries, or fatalities, especially in emergency braking situations.
symptoms: The brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the brake pedal goes to the floor before the brakes engage
increased stopping distance
and the vehicle may shake or vibrate when braking.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Erroneous ABS Activation and Vehicle Instability
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The erroneous activation of the ABS system can cause the vehicle to suddenly decelerate or stop, leading to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: The ABS system activates without warning
the vehicle suddenly decelerates or stops
the vehicle stability control warning light illuminates
and the vehicle may shake or vibrate when braking.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Brake Failure and Loss of Stopping Power
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake system can lead to accidents, injuries, or fatalities, especially in emergency braking situations.
symptoms: The brakes fail to engage
the vehicle does not stop or slows down slowly
and the brake pedal may feel soft or spongy.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the sliding doors can cause injuries, especially to children, and damage to the vehicle.
symptoms: The doors may not open or close properly
fall off
or become detached from the track.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The peeling and flaking of paint can lead to rust and corrosion, reducing the vehicle's value and potentially causing safety issues.
symptoms: Large areas of paint peeling and flaking off the hood
roof
and other parts of the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the liftgate struts can cause injuries, especially to the head and neck, and damage to the vehicle.
symptoms: The liftgate may not stay open
fall suddenly
or require manual effort to open and close.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The fuel pump module leak can cause fuel leaks, fires, and engine stalling, leading to accidents and injuries.
symptoms: Fuel leaks
engine stalling
and difficulty starting the engine.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The tailgate gas leakage can cause the tailgate to fall suddenly, leading to injuries and damage to the vehicle.
symptoms: The tailgate may not stay open or may fall suddenly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The transmission slipping or jerking can cause the vehicle to lose power, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The transmission slips or jerks when shifting gears
feels like the vehicle is hesitating or stuttering
vibrates or shudders when accelerating
and may cause the vehicle to lose power or stall.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Unintended acceleration can cause the vehicle to lose control, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The vehicle accelerates suddenly and unexpectedly
often when the brake pedal is pressed
and may cause the vehicle to jerk or lurch forward.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Brake system failure can cause the vehicle to lose control, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The brakes fail to engage properly
causing the vehicle to slow down or stop unexpectedly
and may cause the vehicle to jerk or lurch forward.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: ESC system failure can cause the vehicle to lose control, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The ESC system fails to engage properly
causing the vehicle to lose traction or stability
and may cause the vehicle to jerk or lurch forward.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Torque converter failure can cause the transmission to slip or jerk, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The torque converter fails
causing the transmission to slip or jerk
and may cause the vehicle to lose power or stall.
